[4] Diarrhea - Uganda (Obongi Country)
Date: Fri 17 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200603160917.html>

Uganda: Strange Disease Kills 2 in Moyo
-----------------------------------------------
An abdominal infection with symptoms like those of cholera has killed 2
people in Maduga village, Obongi County. 13 others have been admitted in
critical condition to Obongi Health Center.
The signs of the disease include vomiting, watery diarrhea and rapid
dehydration. Dr Sarafin A'dibaku, the District Director of Health Services
yesterday 16 Mar 2006 said the 1st victim of the unknown infection died on
11 Mar 2006, while the 2nd died on Wed 15 Mar 2006.
A'dibaku ruled out earlier reports that the disease could be cholera.
"It is a kind of diarrhea we cannot explain, but certainly, it is not
cholera. We have just sent stool and other specimens for examination to the
government laboratory in Kampala," A'dibaku said.
He said with cholera, a patient in critical condition either dies or
recovers quickly.
"But the people admitted at Obongi Health Centre have been there for almost
a week," A'dibaku said.
Daily Monitor has learned that health educators have been put on high alert
and dispatched to inform the residents about proper hygiene practices to
prevent further spread of the illness.
In a bid to avoid getting the infection, the residents have abandoned the
tradition of shaking hands while greeting.
[Byline: Tabu Butagira]
--
