[5] Cholera - Angola (Luanda)
Date: Wed 15 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: XinHuaNet.com [edited]
<http://english.people.com.cn/200603/15/eng20060315_250715.html>

Cholera outbreak in Angolan capital hits 231 people
-----------------------------------------------
The cholera outbreak sweeping through the poorest districts of the Angolan
capital of Luanda has struck 231 people, but the number of deaths resulting
from the epidemic has not risen for over a week, officials have said.
In its latest update on Mon 13 Mar 2006 on Luanda's cholera outbreak in a
month, the WHO said 39 new cases had been recorded in the past 72 hours,
according to local reports on Tue 14 Mar 2006.
The epidemic broke out on 13 Feb 2006 in the Boavista district of the
capital and has caused 11 deaths, mostly in the 1st days of the outbreak.
