[6] Diarrhea - Botswana
Date: Mon 6 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: SABCNews.com [edited]
<http://www.sabcnews.com/africa/southern_africa/0,2172,123254,00.html>

Concern for SA as Botswana diarrhea escalates
-----------------------------------------------
Concern is mounting that the massive outbreak of diarrhea in neighboring
Botswana could spill over into South Africa. Since January 2006, 191 deaths
from diarrhea have been recorded in Botswana, among more than 10 000 cases,
most of them in children younger than 5.
Colo Boitshoko, a spokesperson for the Botswana health ministry, struggled
to answer a question on whether the outbreak has already crossed our borders.
Boitshoko said: "It depends on what the cause is. Right now, I can't tell
you whether it will affect South Africa, but I think I've heard in the news
sometime that South Africa is also affected by the disease to a large
extent, to a certain extent; I don't know how exactly it is. It depends on
what causes it."
--
