[7] Diarrhea - India (Mumbai)
Date: Sun 20 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: ZeeNews.com [edited]
<http://www.zeenews.com/znnew/articles.asp?aid=282714&sid=REG>

20 new gastro cases reported in Mumbai; cholera report soon
-----------------------------------------------
20 new cases of gastroenteritis were reported in Mumbai (Bombay) today, 20
Mar 2006, even as doctors maintained that reports of cholera could not be
confirmed until tomorrow, when test results were expected.
"20 new cases have been admitted in 4 government-run hospitals today, 20
Mar 2006, while 16 patients have been discharged. We have conducted
preliminary test on 4 patients for possible cholera, but it cannot be
confirmed until the final test results arrive," the dean of JJ Hospital,
Pravin Shingare, said.
More than 173 patients had been admitted with gastro symptoms in various
city hospitals since the past week, mainly from Crawford Market area of
south Mumbai. Since then, several have been discharged.
All of them complained of diarrhea and vomiting, common gastro symptoms.
Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) health department officials
earlier ruled out the possibility of food poisoning and said the possible
cause of the gastro outbreak could be a contaminated water supply.
--
