[8] Cholera - India (Mumbai)
Date: Sat 18 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Times of India [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/1454447.cms>

_Vibrio cholerae_ found in 68 yr old
-----------------------------------------
A 68-year-old man from Mazgaon, found infected with a _Vibrio cholerae_
strain by a private laboratory, is now recuperating at a private hospital
in Byculla.
As the Mazgaon businessman recuperated, public hospitals awaited results
confirming whether the cholera bacteria had hit south Mumbai. The man
initially ignored the bouts of vomiting and loose stools that started on
Sunday night, 12 Mar 2006.
"But he did not get any better the next day and became weaker. So we rushed
him to hospital," his brother said. Doctors at the hospital were shocked by
Sadiq's rapid deterioration.
Doctors got worried when the infection began to affect his kidneys, and his
body refused to respond to standard treatment. A stool test conducted on
Tue 14 Mar 2006 produced the alarming finding: "_Vibrio cholerae_ isolated."
--
