[9] Cholera - India (Mumbai)
Date: Thu 16 Mar 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Mumbai Newsline [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=173963>

3 test positive for cholera
-----------------------------
3 of the 170 patients admitted to 5 state and civic-run hospitals with
suspected gastroenteritis tested positive for cholera on Thu 16 Mar 2006,
after their stool samples were tested at St George Hospital.
All 3 patients -- a watchman, a 4-year-old girl and a helper at Crawford
Market -- are South Mumbai residents and were admitted to the hospital on
Tue and Wed, 14-15 Mar 2006.
"3 samples have tested positive for cholera bacteria'" confirmed Dr Pravin
Shingare, dean of the JJ Group of Hospitals, which include JJ, Cama,
Gokuldas Tejpal and St George hospitals. "But it's only a preliminary test.
The samples will be sent for stool culture tests, and the results will be
available after 48 hours." The samples may be sent to the National
Institute of Virology in Pune.
As the number of gastroenteritis cases jumped to 170 -- more than double
the Wed 15 Mar 2006 figure of 69 patients -- with people from Colaba,
Carnac Bunder, Paltan Road, Samuel Street, Kalbadevi, Bhuleshwar, Mandvi
Koliwada, Chira Bazar and Thakurdwar streaming into hospitals, Municipal
Commissioner Johny Joseph said 47 water samples had been collected from
overhead tanks and taps in several South Mumbai chawls.
[Byline: Swati Ali]
--
